04:31.543 --> 04:34.712
and I'll... I'll come over there.

04:34.746 --> 04:36.213
(Grimacing and grunting) Oh! Ooh, baby.

04:36.247 --> 04:37.782
Ooh, wow. Ugh.

04:40.385 --> 04:44.789
Yikes! That's... That hurts today.

04:44.823 --> 04:48.258
Yeah, Roland, he told me
about your back and I...

04:48.293 --> 04:50.227
I am so sorry.

04:50.261 --> 04:52.662
Well... well, I'm the one who's sorry, Bob.

04:52.696 --> 04:56.800
You know, hearing about your,
uh, brother... C-C-Chris-

04:56.834 --> 04:59.002
- Carl.
- Carl. Yeah, he was a good man.

04:59.037 --> 05:00.703
A good man. He admired you, Johnny.

05:00.738 --> 05:01.805
And I him. Yeah.

05:01.839 --> 05:03.640
And I him.

05:03.674 --> 05:05.875
Listen, uh, I understand about your back...

05:05.910 --> 05:07.978
Yeah... (Grimaces)

05:08.012 --> 05:11.181
And... I was just uh.. Just wondering

05:11.215 --> 05:14.250
if, uh, maybe you could say
a few words at the funeral?

05:14.284 --> 05:16.920
(Coughs)

05:16.954 --> 05:19.322
Well, the thing, uh, the thing is, uh, Bob,

05:19.356 --> 05:22.559
I-I-I don't feel I
deserve that... honor.

05:22.593 --> 05:26.028
Oh, see, I'm uh... I'm
no good at these things.

05:26.063 --> 05:29.231
You know, you, you're... You're polished.

05:29.266 --> 05:31.100
You know, you're... You're well-spoken.

05:31.134 --> 05:33.069
Oh no. No, no. Not really. Not really.

05:33.103 --> 05:35.605
I mean, I'm good one on one,

05:35.639 --> 05:37.539
but not-not good in a public situation.

05:37.574 --> 05:38.941
I clam up pret-pretty good.

05:38.976 --> 05:41.143
As a favor, Johnny.

05:41.178 --> 05:43.245
He must have had a few close friends,

05:43.280 --> 05:46.515
- somebody that
- No one.

05:46.549 --> 05:49.452
Well, sure. Sure. I can
say a few words, Bob.

05:49.486 --> 05:52.721
I'll say a few words.

05:52.755 --> 05:55.824
(Music plays quietly,
approaching footsteps)

05:55.859 --> 05:58.494
Have you seen the couple that checked in?

05:58.528 --> 06:02.531
They're like really scummy.
Like... very skaggy people,

06:02.565 --> 06:05.400
who happened to produce a child

06:05.434 --> 06:07.302
that hasn't been taken away from them yet.

06:07.336 --> 06:08.871
Imagine being related to them.

06:08.905 --> 06:10.639
No, I can't. It's too early.

06:10.673 --> 06:15.210
- They're my cousins.
- Oh! Well, the um...

06:15.244 --> 06:17.545
The baby's relatively normal looking.

06:17.579 --> 06:18.946
No, no they're definitely skaggy.

06:18.981 --> 06:22.282
My God, they're so skaggy.

06:22.317 --> 06:24.418
Hmm. Wait, so you're related to Carl?

06:24.452 --> 06:26.654
Not genetically.

06:26.688 --> 06:30.090
My mom's sister was married to
Carl. Carl is Sean's step-dad.

06:30.125 --> 06:31.526
And was that a factor
in the cause of death?

06:31.560 --> 06:34.094
I wouldn't be surprised.

06:34.129 --> 06:36.530
They broke up just before
Sean got Bree pregnant.

06:36.564 --> 06:38.999
Or someone got Bree pregnant.

06:39.033 --> 06:41.034
I mean, Bree's not exactly fussy

06:41.068 --> 06:44.037
when it comes to introducing
men to her vagina.

06:44.071 --> 06:45.471
Mm. Charming.

06:45.506 --> 06:48.241
(Car rumbles by)

06:48.275 --> 06:50.877
(Bag thumps on chair)

06:50.912 --> 06:53.947
Tell me it's not always this clean in here.

06:53.981 --> 06:55.015
No, it's-it's always this clean.

06:55.049 --> 06:57.716
Oh... it smells so fresh!

06:57.751 --> 06:59.585
Uh... that's the Febreeze.

06:59.619 --> 07:01.787
I was... I was eating
Indian last night, so...

07:01.821 --> 07:04.323
So much better than the motel.

07:04.358 --> 07:07.026
At least you know what the smell is.

07:07.061 --> 07:08.994
(Squeals happily)

07:09.029 --> 07:10.029
(Kissing)

07:12.732 --> 07:14.100
(Paws skitter across on floor)

07:14.134 --> 07:15.900
Oh, ho-oh! Oh... (Laughs)

07:15.935 --> 07:18.002
Hey, come on now, you two, Oh, hi! Hi.

07:18.037 --> 07:20.638
- Come on.
- Hi there. Ooh!

07:20.673 --> 07:24.042
Oh-ho-ho... there's a good
girl. There's a good girl!

07:24.077 --> 07:27.845
- They're so...
- Well, Macy and Fifer are just staying with me

07:27.880 --> 07:29.314
for a couple of weeks until
they get back on their feet.

07:29.348 --> 07:31.283
Isn't that right, Fifey?

07:31.317 --> 07:33.518
Yeah, your worms are almost
all gone, aren't they?

07:33.553 --> 07:35.419
Yeah...

07:35.454 --> 07:37.521
Is that a diaper on that little cutie?

07:37.556 --> 07:40.691
Yup. Oh! You know what though? Whoa
-'kay. This is just...

07:40.725 --> 07:42.759
This is because she's...
She's... She's scared right now.

07:42.794 --> 07:44.295
But don't worry.

07:44.329 --> 07:46.330
I can tell that you
are gonna win them over.

07:46.364 --> 07:48.566
- Yeah... ?
- Yeah.

07:48.600 --> 07:51.935
I just-I haven't um...
been... I haven't-I don't-

07:51.970 --> 07:53.769
I'm not around dogs a lot,
so... (Laughs nervously)

07:53.804 --> 07:54.670
No, you know what? Don't even worry about.

07:54.705 --> 07:56.906
Just... for tonight,

07:56.940 --> 07:59.476
think of them as... our kids. (Dogs pant)

07:59.510 --> 08:02.378
Right? Oh yeah...

08:02.413 --> 08:04.481
John, you're speaking at the funeral?

08:04.515 --> 08:07.217
