13:57.569 --> 13:59.170
Don't worry, I threw out the remote.

13:59.204 --> 14:00.638
Hmm.

14:02.874 --> 14:04.508
Well, it looks like
they have a side hustle.

14:04.543 --> 14:07.945
Uh, I'm pretty sure she strips. Why?

14:07.979 --> 14:10.113
Oh no, this is just a lot of um...

14:10.148 --> 14:13.283
- Yes, it is.
- Marijuana. (Sniffs)

14:13.317 --> 14:15.586
And if you're offering, my answer is yes.

14:15.620 --> 14:17.021
(Bag rustles)

14:22.193 --> 14:24.528
Thank you for that, Shannon.

14:24.562 --> 14:28.097
Nothing says we'll miss you like
an excerpt from "Breaking Dawn,"

14:28.131 --> 14:30.466
one of Carl's favourites
of the Twilight movies.

14:30.500 --> 14:31.634
(Mourner cries, baby wails)

14:31.669 --> 14:34.303
Now, to say a few words,

14:34.337 --> 14:36.272
I'd like to bring up a close friend

14:36.306 --> 14:38.140
and one of Carl's personal heroes...

14:38.175 --> 14:39.943
(Baby wails)

14:39.977 --> 14:41.510
Johnny Rose. (Mourners clap and murmur)

14:44.747 --> 14:46.848
(Baby wails, mourner coughs)

14:50.053 --> 14:51.587
Thank you... minister.

14:53.656 --> 14:57.059
Carl...

14:57.093 --> 14:58.526
What to say about Carl... ?

15:00.997 --> 15:04.299
Once so full of life

15:04.333 --> 15:07.735
and now... lying... very, very close to me.

15:10.038 --> 15:11.706
What a terrible thing death is...

15:14.076 --> 15:17.078
And yet, for Carl,

15:17.112 --> 15:19.113
pretty much an all-consuming
thing at this point.

15:19.147 --> 15:21.048
(Mourner cries)

15:21.083 --> 15:23.084
He-he was a- he was
a man who loved...

15:25.186 --> 15:26.553
A good sweater I'm told.

15:29.056 --> 15:31.558
And-and he loved the feel
of big tool in his hand,

15:31.593 --> 15:34.161
am I right, Bob?

15:34.195 --> 15:36.563
And I wonder,

15:36.598 --> 15:40.199
when Carl was spinning
around on that ceiling fan

15:40.234 --> 15:42.935
that he was so very proud of,

15:42.969 --> 15:46.539
was he ever thinking of this town...

15:46.573 --> 15:49.342
where he was born where he lived,

15:49.376 --> 15:51.477
and where he died... Where he died.

15:55.382 --> 15:58.484
But I-I-I'm not
up here today

15:58.519 --> 16:02.720
to speak about dying in Schitt's Creek.

16:02.755 --> 16:06.991
(Cell phone rings)
I'm-I'm here-I'm-

16:07.026 --> 16:09.327
(Phone beeps on) (Bleep!)
Where the hell are you, Sean?!

16:09.362 --> 16:11.630
At a bar?!

16:11.664 --> 16:13.298
If anyone should be in
a bar right now, it's me.

16:13.332 --> 16:14.732
(Baby wails)

16:14.767 --> 16:17.169
(Bleep) Sean! (Mourners gasp)

16:17.203 --> 16:21.540
(Baby wails) Excuse me.

16:21.574 --> 16:25.075
Well... I-I am here to talk
about dying in Schitt's Creek!

16:25.109 --> 16:28.679
I'm here to talk about the
misery of our lives here

16:28.713 --> 16:31.715
and how we might never escape this place,

16:31.749 --> 16:34.652
and how we do not wanna end
up in a coffin, like Carl,

16:34.686 --> 16:37.754
here in this... godforsaken-

16:37.789 --> 16:41.158
♪ Oh, Danny boy, ♪

16:43.461 --> 16:48.799
♪ the pipes, the pipes are calling... ♪

16:53.104 --> 16:57.007
♪ From Glen to Glen
♪ (Mourners join in)

16:57.041 --> 16:59.542
♪ And down the Mountain side ♪

17:02.714 --> 17:04.748
(making up lyrics) ♪ but God... ♪

17:06.281 --> 17:08.050
(Birds chirp)

17:08.085 --> 17:11.220
So... I'm sorry

17:11.253 --> 17:15.290
if, earlier, I wasn't
sensitive to your animal issues.

17:15.325 --> 17:18.060
And if it's any consolation,
the dogs told me to tell you

17:18.095 --> 17:22.330
that they're super embarrassed
about their behaviour, too.

17:22.365 --> 17:25.767
Well, I am dating a vet.
I should've known that...

17:25.800 --> 17:28.136
There'd be slutty little
animals running around.

17:28.170 --> 17:30.004
And I only take in the slutty ones, so...

17:30.039 --> 17:31.672
(Laughs)

17:31.707 --> 17:33.374
I just... I didn't know what to do

17:33.408 --> 17:36.377
because I love the dogs so much, but...

17:36.411 --> 17:40.949
You know, I also really love...

17:40.983 --> 17:45.653
The way that our relationship
is going right now... so much.

17:45.687 --> 17:48.155
Mm... such a sweet face. (Both laugh)

17:48.189 --> 17:50.691
So, to get you more
comfortable around animals...

17:50.726 --> 17:52.693
Not a puppy, Ted! I...

17:52.728 --> 17:54.328
No, that would be cruel to the puppy.

17:54.363 --> 17:56.697
No, I got you... this.

17:59.434 --> 18:01.969
"Opening your heart to
animals: A guide to the benefits

18:02.003 --> 18:05.038
of caring for something
other than yourself."

18:05.073 --> 18:06.774
It's a very specific book.

18:06.808 --> 18:09.843
You might wanna check out page 37.

18:09.878 --> 18:10.878
(Pages flip)

18:13.047 --> 18:14.681
(Whispers excitedly) Is it a credit card?

18:14.715 --> 18:17.651
No. It's a room key...

18:17.685 --> 18:20.320
To the premium king suite

18:20.354 --> 18:22.389
at the Holiday Inn Express in Elmdale,

18:22.423 --> 18:25.125
and they have a very strict
no pets allowed policy.

18:25.160 --> 18:27.660
Well... it just so happens

18:27.694 --> 18:30.062
that I have packed my overnight bag.

18:30.097 --> 18:32.165
- Hmm.
- Come here.

18:32.199 --> 18:35.101
(Kiss)

18:35.135 --> 18:36.702
- Thank you.
- No. Thank you.

18:36.736 --> 18:38.137
- No. Thank you!
- Thank you.

18:38.172 --> 18:38.871
- Thank you!
- Thank you.

18:38.906 --> 18:39.906
Thank you!

18:39.940 --> 18:41.473
(Bird chirp)

18:44.211 --> 18:45.477
You know where I got my hat, brah?

18:45.512 --> 18:47.179
Where?

18:47.213 --> 18:49.281
"Assholes' R 'Us".

18:49.315 --> 18:51.116
(Both giggle)

18:51.150 --> 18:53.584
(Laughing)

18:57.056 --> 18:59.191
(Car doors bang shut outside) Oh! Ow!

18:59.225 --> 19:01.759
(Baby wails outside) Oh! Oh my God.

19:01.794 --> 19:03.829
Oh my God! We need to go.

19:03.863 --> 19:05.830
We need to go! We need to go!

19:08.333 --> 19:10.400
(Panicked whisper) I don't
see it... I don't see it.

19:10.435 --> 19:11.501
- Let me see
it- - Shhh...

19:11.536 --> 19:13.437
(Keys jingle, lock tumbles)

19:13.471 --> 19:14.604
(Panicked breaths)

19:16.908 --> 19:18.342
(Door bangs shut, baby wails)

19:18.376 --> 19:19.977
The (Bleep)?!

19:20.011 --> 19:21.651
Shhhhhh!  (Stifled laughter)

19:26.084 --> 19:27.784
(Whispering) My hat.. I'm wearing it.

19:27.819 --> 19:29.052
I'm wearing it...

19:29.086 --> 19:30.753
(Stifles a laugh)

19:30.787 --> 19:32.488
(Both laughing)

19:34.825 --> 19:36.159
(Kissing, Stevie slams into door)

19:36.193 --> 19:38.033
(Beer bottle scrape door,
Stevie grunts softly)

19:38.996 --> 19:41.464
(Panting and kissing)

19:44.034 --> 19:44.767
(Crash)

19:54.111 --> 19:55.344
So I'm thinking to myself,

19:55.378 --> 19:57.814
"Oh, God, what if die here?"

19:57.848 --> 20:01.184
Mm. That was not lost on anyone.

20:01.218 --> 20:03.152
Uh, let's pilfer a few sandwiches

20:03.187 --> 20:04.753
and make a gracious French exit.

20:04.788 --> 20:06.588
Good idea.

20:10.193 --> 20:14.661
Moira! Your "Danny Boy"... What a voice.

20:14.964 --> 20:16.665
- Oh, thank you.
- Yeah.

20:16.700 --> 20:18.834
I-I'd really like you to
sing at my cousin's funeral.

20:18.868 --> 20:20.336
She's not dead, but...

20:20.370 --> 20:23.372
She's been coughing a lot lately.

20:23.406 --> 20:25.808
Moira, before they close the coffin,

20:25.842 --> 20:28.210
One more chorus for Carl?

20:28.244 --> 20:30.511
Please?

20:30.546 --> 20:31.912
(Chuckles awkwardly)

20:31.947 --> 20:34.915
(Mourners laugh and clap)

20:34.950 --> 20:36.451
Take your time, honey.

20:36.485 --> 20:38.386
(Clears throat awkwardly)

20:41.790 --> 20:44.959
♪ Ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh,
ooh-ooh-ooh ooh ooh... ♪

20:47.528 --> 20:50.029
♪ Oh... ♪ (Inhales deeply)

20:52.032 --> 20:54.401
♪ Danny... ♪

20:57.638 --> 20:59.305
(Silence)

21:01.041 --> 21:02.476
♪ Boy... ♪

21:04.211 --> 21:06.012
(Chewing loudly)

21:06.046 --> 21:08.982
♪ The pipes, the pipes are... ♪

21:11.518 --> 21:13.719
♪ Call-all-all-ling... ♪

21:13.720 --> 21:15.288
It's our annual

21:15.290 --> 21:17.323
Hawaiian night.

21:17.325 --> 21:19.259
Pineapples, pig on the spit,

21:19.261 --> 21:20.593
the whole nine yards.

21:20.595 --> 21:22.428
Oh, you, uh, roast pig?

21:22.430 --> 21:23.897
We do!

21:23.899 --> 21:25.765
So, who's pig do we have to

21:25.767 --> 21:26.832
slaughter to get an invite?

